  "prompt": "How to recover/restore imei numbers on Android erased from command \"fastboot erase all\" ?",
  "response": "Restoring IMEI numbers that have been erased using the command `fastboot erase all` can be a challenging issue. This command wipes all partitions, including those containing modem firmware and IMEI information. Here\u2019s a comprehensive approach to potentially restore your IMEI:\n\n### Warning:\n1. **Legal Notice**: Changing or tampering with IMEI numbers can be illegal in many jurisdictions. Make sure you are compliant with local laws.\n2. **Bricking Risk**: Changes to your device firmware can lead to bricking your device. Proceed with caution.\n\n### Steps to Restore IMEI:\n\n#### 1. **Identify Your Device Model**\nFirst, make sure you know the exact model of your device. Different devices may have different methods for restoring the IMEI.\n\n#### 2. **Backup Your Data**\nIf possible, back up any important data before you proceed with recovery efforts.\n\n#### 3. **Reflash Stock Firmware**\nReflashing the stock firmware can sometimes restore the missing IMEI. \n\n- Download the official firmware for your device model from the manufacturer\u2019s site or a trusted source.\n- Use tools like **Odin** (for Samsung devices), **SP Flash Tool** (for MediaTek devices), or others relevant to your device brand to flash the firmware.\n\n#### 4. **Using EFS Backup**\nIf you had previously made an EFS backup (which contains sensitive data including the IMEI), you can restore it:\n\n- Use a tool like **TWRP** (Team Win Recovery Project) to flash the EFS backup.\n- If you have a TWRP backup, boot your device into recovery mode and restore the EFS partition from your backup.\n\n#### 5. **Using ADB and Terminal Applications**\nYou can sometimes set the IMEI back using specific tools on rooted devices:\n\n- **Root your device** if it\u2019s not already rooted.\n- Use terminal commands or applications like **MTK Engineering Mode** (for MediaTek devices) or **IMEI Changer** apps, but verify their compatibility.\n\n```sh\nsu\nadb shell\nservice call iphonesubinfo\n```\nThen follow the app instructions to set the IMEI number.\n\n#### 6. **Using Qualcomm Tool**\nFor Qualcomm-based devices, you can use specialized tools such as QFIL/QGDP.\n\n1. Install the tool and appropriate drivers for your device.\n2. Use the tool to flash the correct IMEI data.\n\n#### 7. **Contact Manufacturer or Service Provider**\nIf you're unable to restore the IMEI using the aforementioned methods, your best bet might be to contact the manufacturer\u2019s customer service or a professional repair service. They may have specialized tools or processes to restore the IMEI.\n\n### Conclusion\nIMEI number recovery can vary widely based on the device model and chipset. Always ensure you're following legal guidelines and utilizing official resources where possible. If unsure, seek professional help.",
